reviewText: This was a wonderful performance by the classic duo at their height of their creativity (and popularity).  It was from the early eighties.  I did buy this concert video on VHS, though, and it was slightly worn, and the picture quality was sometimes poor.  Other than that, I loved the concert!  It seemed to be from around the "H2O" album time -- and included most of their hits up till then.  The bad was great, with GE Smith, and the harmony singing is wonderful.  Real soulful!
